1
00:00:04,677 --> 00:00:07,986
But what is preventing this,
is this ego:

2
00:00:07,986 --> 00:00:12,387
“I’m nobody’s servant,
I don’t bow down to anyone.”

3
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:16,673
[I Need Help!]

4
00:00:16,698 --> 00:00:19,633
And it’s not even true.

5
00:00:21,765 --> 00:00:26,899
It’s just posturing.

6
00:00:29,499 --> 00:00:34,283
We bow down all the time
to all sorts of people,

7
00:00:34,289 --> 00:00:36,421
and to all sorts
of circumstances.

8
00:00:36,421 --> 00:00:39,236
We’re humbled, 
we’re humiliated.

9
00:00:39,486 --> 00:00:42,054
Not just humbled.
Humiliated.

10
00:00:42,054 --> 00:00:45,962
Prabhupād says in one of his purports
in the Bhagavad-gītā,

11
00:00:45,962 --> 00:00:50,902
“When one realizes 
that material existence

12
00:00:50,902 --> 00:00:56,893
is a constant source of perplexity
at every step,

13
00:00:56,893 --> 00:01:03,246
it behooves such a person
to approach a spiritual master.”

14
00:01:03,930 --> 00:01:09,670
So, we have this ego
that won’t allow us to admit,

15
00:01:09,685 --> 00:01:14,480
“I’m lost.
What to speak of others,

16
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:18,214
I can’t even
take care of myself.

17
00:01:18,994 --> 00:01:21,044
I need help!”

